msgid ""
"The edit screen enables you to edit the take of a verse or chunk in the "
"following ways:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:253
msgid "`Comparing your recording to the source audio`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:254
msgid "`Cutting`_ sections of a recording"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:255
msgid "`Inserting`_ new sections into a recording"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:256
msgid "`Placing verse markers`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:257
msgid "`Rating`_ the recording"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:259
msgid ""
"The Edit screen contains several icons to perform this functionality, as "
"shown below:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:261
msgid "Edit screen icons"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:268
msgid "Comparing your recording to the source audio"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:270
msgid ""
"If you have source audio, you can compare the target language recording "
"to the source audio to see what, if anything, needs to be changed in your"
" translation. Perform the following steps:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:272
msgid "Tap the **Ear icon** to switch to Source Audio."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:273
msgid "Tap the **Play icon** on the gray bar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:274
msgid ""
"To pause the recording tap the **Pause icon** on the gray bar (the Pause "
"icon replaces the Play icon when the audio is playing.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:275
msgid ""
"To rewind (go towards the beginning of the recording) or fast forward (go"
" towards the end of the recording) tap and hold the **green dot** and "
"slide your finger to the left for rewind or to the right to fast forward."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:276
msgid "To return to your recording, tap the **Waveform icon**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:277
msgid "Then, listen to the recording:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:279
msgid ""
"``a.``      To playback your recording, tap the white **Play icon** on "
"the blue bar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:281
msgid ""
"``b.``      To pause the playback of the recording, tap the **Pause "
"icon** on the blue bar. (The Pause icon replaces the Play icon.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:283
msgid ""
"``c.``      To rewind to the beginning of the recording or go to the end "
"of the recording tap the **Rewind** or **Forward** icon."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:285
msgid ""
"Tap between the source audio (Ear icon) and target language (Waveform "
"icon) playback to compare the entire recording."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:289
msgid "Cutting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:291
msgid "The action of removing a section of a recording is known as a \"cut\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:293
msgid ""
"To make the cut you first mark the section to be deleted. There are 2 "
"ways to mark a section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:295
msgid "The first way is to use the upper waveform window:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:297
msgid ""
"``a.``      Position the audio at the thin blue line for the beginning of"
" the recording to be removed. **NOTE**: The blue line does not move. You "
"need to do the tap-and-hold action to move the recording to the blue "
"line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:299
msgid ""
"``b.``      Tap the **Flag icon** to set the beginning point of the cut. "
"This inserts a marker where the cut will start."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:301
msgid ""
"``c.``      Drag the recording by holding your finger on the screen and "
"sliding to the left until the end of the part to be removed is at the "
"blue line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:303
msgid ""
"``d.``      Tap the upside-down **Flag icon**. This marks the end of the "
"section for deletion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:305
msgid ""
"The second way to mark a section for deletion is by using the entire "
"waveform that is displayed in the lower section of the window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:307
msgid ""
"``a.``      Tap and hold where you want the deletion to begin and drag to"
" the end of the deletion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:309
msgid ""
"``b.``      As you do so, the marked area is shown in both the upper and "
"lower waveform areas and the flags are inserted automatically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:311
msgid ""
"**OPTIONAL**: Tap the **Play icon** to listen to the section that will be"
" removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:313
msgid ""
"**Do you want to change the amount of recording that is selected?** Tap-"
"hold-drag on the upside-down flag to increase or decrease the amount of "
"the selected recording."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:315
msgid ""
"**Need to start again?** Tap the **Crossed-off Flags** icon to remove the"
" flags and start at step 1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:317
msgid "Tap the **Scissors icon** to cut the section you have marked for deletion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:319
msgid ""
"**OPTIONAL**: Tap **Play** to listen to the take to ensure it is correct."
" If you made a mistake, tap the **Undo icon** to restore the deleted "
"section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:321
msgid ""
"Tap the **Save icon** to save the edit. BTT Recorder saves the edited "
"take and returns to Project Management."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:324
msgid "Inserting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:326
msgid ""
"Sometimes you may want to insert a missing part into the translation. For"
" example, to re-record a section of the take, you can first cut it and "
"then insert the replacement for the section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:328
msgid "To insert a section into the recording, perform the following steps:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:330
msgid ""
"Position the audio at the thin blue line for where the new audio will be "
"added in (use the tap-hold-drag action, or tap in the lower waveform, or "
"listen to the recording and tap **Pause** when you are at the correct "
"place.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:331
msgid ""
"Tap the **Add a Recording** icon   in the top gray bar. This opens a new "
"recording session for the part to be inserted. **NOTE**: The bar at the "
"bottom of this window is green."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:332
msgid "Tap the **Microphone icon** to start recording."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:333
msgid "When finished, tap the **Pause icon**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:334
msgid "To insert the new recording, tap the **Checkmark icon**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:335
msgid "A pop up appears stating it is inserting recording … please wait."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:336
msgid ""
"The original target language recording opens with the inserted recording "
"added."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:337
msgid "To save the file tap the **Save icon**. A ‘Saving’ pop-up appears."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:339
msgid ""
"Once the program is done saving, the Project Management verse/chunk list "
"screen opens with a new take added at the bottom of the take list. For "
"example, if there were 3 takes before recording the new section, the "
"added take is Take 4."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:342
msgid "Placing verse markers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:344
msgid ""
"Verse markers are available only when recordings are done in chunk mode. "
"To insert the verse markers, perform the following steps:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:346
msgid "Open the recording in the Edit screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:347
msgid "Tap on the bookmark icon. The Verse Marker window opens."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:348
msgid "Notice the yellow playback bar on the bottom of the window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:349
msgid "The top gray bar has the number of markers left to put into place."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:350
msgid "A verse marker is at the beginning of the recording."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:351
msgid "Locate the end of the verse:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:352
msgid "Tap the **Play icon** to play back the recording."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:353
msgid "Tap the **Pause icon** to stop the playback when it is at a verse ending."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:354
msgid "Other ways of finding the correct spot in the recording:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:355
msgid ""
"Use the tap-hold-drag action to move the playback forward or backward "
"until the verse division is on the blue line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:356
msgid "OR"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:357
msgid "Tap in the bottom waveform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:358
msgid ""
"To add the verse marker, tap the **white flag** on the yellow bar at the "
"bottom right of the screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:359
msgid ""
"If there is another verse to mark: Continue to listen to the playback for"
" the next ending of a verse."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:360
msgid ""
"If you need to move a verse marker, you can use the tap-hold-drag action "
"to move a verse marker flag forward or backward on the waveform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:361
msgid ""
"When there are no more verse markers to place – tap the X icon at the top"
" left of the window, just to the left of where it tells you the number of"
" markers left to be placed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:362
msgid ""
"The Edit screen opens and shows the verse markers. Tap the **Save icon** "
"at the bottom right of the screen to save and return to Project "
"Management."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:364
msgid "**HINT**: You might want to rate this recording before saving."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:367
msgid "Rating"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:369
msgid ""
"To indicate the quality of the recording, you can add a star rating to "
"it. The star ratings are used by the program to determine which take of a"
" verse or chunk to use when compiling an entire chapter recording (see "
"`Creating a Chapter Recording <https://btt-"
"recorder.readthedocs.io/en/latest/compiling.html>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:371
msgid ""
"Tap the Star icon (either on the verse/chunk bar or in the top gray bar "
"of the edit window). The ‘Rate this take’ window opens."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:372
msgid "Decide on a rating:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:374
msgid "Tap the left star if the recording is not the best – the star turns red."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:375
msgid ""
"Tap the middle star if the recording is fine but could be better – the "
"stars turn yellow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:376
msgid ""
"Tap the right star for an excellent recording – the starts turn green. "
"Only one take per verse/chunk can be rated 3 stars, because this "
"indicates the accepted take."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mainscreens.rst:378
msgid "Tap **OK** to save."
msgstr ""

